39static u32
40gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
41{
42 switch (engine->subdev.index) {
43 case NVKM_ENGINE_SW : return 0;
44 case NVKM_ENGINE_GR : return 0x0210;
45 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE0 : return 0x0230;
46 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE1 : return 0x0240;
47 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC: return 0x0250;
48 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP : return 0x0260;
49 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSVLD : return 0x0270;
50 default:
51 WARN_ON(1);
52 return 0;
53 }
54}
55
56static int
57gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_fini(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
58 struct nvkm_engine *engine, bool suspend)
59{
60 const u32 offset = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(engine);
61 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
62 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &chan->fifo->base.engine.subdev;
63 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
64 struct nvkm_gpuobj *inst = chan->base.inst;
65 int ret = 0;
66
67 mutex_lock(&subdev->mutex);
68 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002634, chan->base.chid);
69 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
70 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002634) == chan->base.chid)
71 break;
72 ) < 0) {
73 nvkm_error(subdev, "channel %d [%s] kick timeout\n",
74 chan->base.chid, chan->base.object.client->name);
75 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
76 }
77 mutex_unlock(&subdev->mutex);
78
79 if (ret && suspend)
80 return ret;
81
82 if (offset) {
83 nvkm_kmap(inst);
84 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x00, 0x00000000);
85 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x04, 0x00000000);
86 nvkm_done(inst);
87 }
88
89 return ret;
90}
91
92static int
93gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_init(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
94 struct nvkm_engine *engine)
95{
96 const u32 offset = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(engine);
97 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
98 struct nvkm_gpuobj *inst = chan->base.inst;
99
100 if (offset) {
101 u64 addr = chan->engn[engine->subdev.index].vma.offset;
102 nvkm_kmap(inst);
103 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x00, lower_32_bits(addr) | 4);
104 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x04, upper_32_bits(addr));
105 nvkm_done(inst);
106 }
107
108 return 0;
109}
110
111static void
112gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_dtor(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
113 struct nvkm_engine *engine)
114{
115 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
116 nvkm_gpuobj_unmap(&chan->engn[engine->subdev.index].vma);
117 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&chan->engn[engine->subdev.index].inst);
118}
119
120static int
121gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_ctor(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
122 struct nvkm_engine *engine,
123 struct nvkm_object *object)
124{
125 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
126 int engn = engine->subdev.index;
127 int ret;
128
129 if (!gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(engine))
130 return 0;
131
132 ret = nvkm_object_bind(object, NULL, 0, &chan->engn[engn].inst);
133 if (ret)
134 return ret;
135
136 return nvkm_gpuobj_map(chan->engn[engn].inst, chan->vm,
137 NV_MEM_ACCESS_RW, &chan->engn[engn].vma);
138}
139
140static void
141gf100_fifo_gpfifo_fini(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base)
142{
143 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
144 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
145 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
146 u32 coff = chan->base.chid * 8;
147
148 if (!list_empty(&chan->head) && !chan->killed) {
149 list_del_init(&chan->head);
150 nvkm_mask(device, 0x003004 + coff, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
151 gf100_fifo_runlist_update(fifo);
152 }
153
154 gf100_fifo_intr_engine(fifo);
155
156 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x003000 + coff, 0x00000000);
157}
158
159static void
160gf100_fifo_gpfifo_init(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base)
161{
162 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
163 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
164 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
165 u32 addr = chan->base.inst->addr >> 12;
166 u32 coff = chan->base.chid * 8;
167
168 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x003000 + coff, 0xc0000000 | addr);
169
170 if (list_empty(&chan->head) && !chan->killed) {
171 list_add_tail(&chan->head, &fifo->chan);
172 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x003004 + coff, 0x001f0001);
173 gf100_fifo_runlist_update(fifo);
174 }
175}
176
177static void *
178gf100_fifo_gpfifo_dtor(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base)
179{
180 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan = gf100_fifo_chan(base);
181 nvkm_vm_ref(NULL, &chan->vm, chan->pgd);
182 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&chan->pgd);
183 return chan;
184}
185
186static const struct nvkm_fifo_chan_func
187gf100_fifo_gpfifo_func = {
188 .dtor = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_dtor,
189 .init = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_init,
190 .fini = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_fini,
191 .ntfy = g84_fifo_chan_ntfy,
192 .engine_ctor = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_ctor,
193 .engine_dtor = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_dtor,
194 .engine_init = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_init,
195 .engine_fini = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_engine_fini,
196};
197
198static int
199gf100_fifo_gpfifo_new(struct nvkm_fifo *base, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
200 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
201{
202 union {
203 struct fermi_channel_gpfifo_v0 v0;
204 } *args = data;
205 struct gf100_fifo *fifo = gf100_fifo(base);
206 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
207 struct nvkm_object *parent = oclass->parent;
208 struct gf100_fifo_chan *chan;
209 u64 usermem, ioffset, ilength;
210 int ret, i;
211
212 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create channel gpfifo size %d\n", size);
213 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
214 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create channel gpfifo vers %d vm %"PRIx64" "
215 "ioffset %016"PRIx64" ilength %08x\n",
216 args->v0.version, args->v0.vm, args->v0.ioffset,
217 args->v0.ilength);
218 } else
219 return ret;
220
221 /* allocate channel */
222 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
223 return -ENOMEM;
224 *pobject = &chan->base.object;
225 chan->fifo = fifo;
226 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&chan->head);
227
228 ret = nvkm_fifo_chan_ctor(&gf100_fifo_gpfifo_func, &fifo->base,
229 0x1000, 0x1000, true, args->v0.vm, 0,
230 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_CE0) |
231 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_CE1) |
232 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_GR) |
233 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC) |
234 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP) |
235 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_MSVLD) |
236 (1ULL << NVKM_ENGINE_SW),
237 1, fifo->user.bar.offset, 0x1000,
238 oclass, &chan->base);
239 if (ret)
240 return ret;
241
242 args->v0.chid = chan->base.chid;
243
244 /* page directory */
245 ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(device, 0x10000, 0x1000, false, NULL, &chan->pgd);
246 if (ret)
247 return ret;
248
249 nvkm_kmap(chan->base.inst);
250 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0200, lower_32_bits(chan->pgd->addr));
251 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0204, upper_32_bits(chan->pgd->addr));
252 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0208, 0xffffffff);
253 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x020c, 0x000000ff);
254 nvkm_done(chan->base.inst);
255
256 ret = nvkm_vm_ref(chan->base.vm, &chan->vm, chan->pgd);
257 if (ret)
258 return ret;
259
260 /* clear channel control registers */
261
262 usermem = chan->base.chid * 0x1000;
263 ioffset = args->v0.ioffset;
264 ilength = order_base_2(args->v0.ilength / 8);
265
266 nvkm_kmap(fifo->user.mem);
267 for (i = 0; i < 0x1000; i += 4)
268 nvkm_wo32(fifo->user.mem, usermem + i, 0x00000000);
269 nvkm_done(fifo->user.mem);
270 usermem = nvkm_memory_addr(fifo->user.mem) + usermem;
271
272 /* RAMFC */
273 nvkm_kmap(chan->base.inst);
274 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x08, lower_32_bits(usermem));
275 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0c, upper_32_bits(usermem));
276 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x10, 0x0000face);
277 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x30, 0xfffff902);
278 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x48, lower_32_bits(ioffset));
279 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x4c, upper_32_bits(ioffset) |
280 (ilength << 16));
281 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x54, 0x00000002);
282 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x84, 0x20400000);
283 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x94, 0x30000001);
284 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x9c, 0x00000100);
285 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xa4, 0x1f1f1f1f);
286 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xa8, 0x1f1f1f1f);
287 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xac, 0x0000001f);
288 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xb8, 0xf8000000);
289 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xf8, 0x10003080); /* 0x002310 */
290 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xfc, 0x10000010); /* 0x002350 */
291 nvkm_done(chan->base.inst);
292 return 0;
293}

295const struct nvkm_fifo_chan_oclass
296gf100_fifo_gpfifo_oclass = {
297 .base.oclass = FERMI_CHANNEL_GPFIFO,
298 .base.minver = 0,
299 .base.maxver = 0,
300 .ctor = gf100_fifo_gpfifo_new,
301};
